title: For Sale:  Polish P-83
postcontent: I have for sale a Polish P-83 Wanad, date stamped 1989. The P-83 was designed as a sidearm for the Polish police and Polish military, and in production from 1983 up to 2000. This P-83 is a single-action/double-action chambered for the 9mm × 18 Makarov round. The construction is all steel with hard rubber grips with a great feel and excellent balance. The trigger pull in Double Action is nice and smooth and the Single Action trigger pull is light and crisp. If you’re looking for a conceal carry weapon the P-83 would work well, especially considering the price. It’s about the same size as a Walther PPK but a little wider in the grip and slide. I’m attracted to these older Eastern European Cold War era arms. I’m as interested in the history of the gun as I am the gun itself.This P-83 is a fantastic shooter, very accurate and field strips ridiculously quick and easily for cleaning. Really, it's a pleasure to shoot this beautiful piece of cold war history.To buy the gun you’ll need a current Wisconsin driver’s license and be at least 18 years of age.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Heckler & Koch FABARM FP6
postcontent: This is an absolutely perfect condition Heckler & Koch FABARM FP6, 12GA, pump shotgun.  This gun has been fired very little and is in as-new condition.  It features a beautiful parkerized finish without a scratch on it, an  integrated picatinny rail on top and a fully threaded barrel with protector nut.  Factory iron sites are included and I have also added an IProtec light mounted and included in the sale.  This gun is one of the most accurate, best patterning shotguns I have ever personally fired.  The action is as smooth as butter and recoil is more than manageable.Price:    $500 OBOSpecifications for this firearm:H&K released the FP6 for military, law enforcement and home defense use.  The machined receiver is manufactured from lightweight Ergal 55 alloy and is drilled and tapped for scope mounting. Three of the four variants were sold with an attached Picatinny rail for mounting optics or accessories and the bottom forward edge of the forend is also drilled to accept an accessory rail. These shotguns are sold with their Tri-bore barrel which is a deep-drilled, machined barrel with three separate internal bore profiles. Beginning at the chamber and forcing cone, the bore is enlarged to .7401" to soften recoil while the second profile is in the middle of the barrel gradually choking down to .7244" to emulate a cylinder bore profile to increase velocity. The final bore is the FABARM choke system which consists of standard choking followed by a cylinder profile at the muzzle which serves to improve shot patterns and distribution.  The muzzle is threaded to accept one of five different chokes or a muzzle brake/compensator. Some models were sold with a ventilated barrel shroud.  Features of the weapon include a chrome-plated trigger, slide release, and shell carrier. There is also an oversized triangular push-button safety. The trigger group is held in the receiver by two pins which makes removal for cleaning and maintenance very easy.
